Title: Paul Francis Leibold
Content: Paul Francis Leibold December 22 1914 – June 1 1972 American clergyman Roman Catholic Church He served archbishop Archdiocese Cincinnati Ohio 1969 1972.Leibold previously served bishop Diocese Evansville Indiana 1966 1969 auxiliary bishop Archdiocese Cincinnati 1958 1966.Paul Leibold born December 22 1914 Dayton Ohio Frank Philomena née Kirchner Leibold He attended Holy Trinity primary school Chaminade High School Dayton Leibold spent two year college University Dayton After deciding enter priesthood entered St. Gregory Seminary finished preparation Mount St. Mary 's Seminary CincinnatiLeibold ordained priest Archdiocese Cincinnati May 18 1940 Archbishop John T. McNicholas He served pastor St. Louis Parish Cincinnati assistant chancellor chancellor archdiocese.In late 1950 's Leibold became spiritual advisor Mildred Ephrem Neuzil nun Our Lady Nativity Convent New Riegel Ohio Between 1956 1959 Neuzil reported Mary mother Jesus appeared several occasion proclaimed Lady America According Neuzil apparition gave message calling Americans return purity Leibold gave approval private devotion Our Lady allowed striking medal honor her.On April 10 1958 Leibold appointed titular bishop Trebenna auxiliary bishop Archdiocese Cincinnati Pope John XXXIII Leibold consecrated June 17 1958 Archbishop Karl Joseph Alter.On April 4 1966 Leibold appointed Pope Paul VI bishop Diocese Evansville He installed June 15 1966.Pope Paul VI appointed Leibold sixth archbishop Archdiocese Cincinnati July 23 1969 He installed October 2 1969 One historian characterized Leibold warm-hearted approachable pastor hard-worker Leibold strengthened Priests Senate Pastoral Council parish council archdiocese He also launched archdiocese 's sixth synod Synod '71.As archbishop Leibold allowed publication two pamphlet Neuzil apparition He also commissioned wooden plaque image Our Lady America display New Riegel convent In September 1971 Leibold criticized composer Leonard Bernstein 's theatrical work Mass terming offensive.Paul Leibold died Good Samaritan Hospital Cincinnati June 1 1972 suffering stroke day He buried Gate Heaven Cemetery Cincinnati Ohio The Bishop Leibold School Miamisburg Ohio Archbishop Leibold Home Aged Cincinnati named him.In 2020 US Conference Catholic Bishops commissioned panel five bishop investigate Neuzil apparition The panel concluded apparition supernatural nature public devotion appropriate

Title: Mandraka Dam
Content: Mandraka Dam gravity dam Mandraka River near Mandraka Analamanga Region Madagascar The dam constructed French firm 1956 creates Lake Mandraka.The dam supply water 24 megawatt 32,000 hp hydroelectric power station 1.9 km 1.2 mi east valley The change elevation dam power station affords hydraulic head 226 metre 741 ft The dam power station operated owned Jirama four 6 megawatt 8,000 hp Pelton turbine-generators commissioned 1958 1972

Title: Joseph Sledge
Content: Joseph Sledge Jr. 1942 – 1 December 2020 American man wrongly convicted murder two woman Josephine Aileen Davis imprisoned 36 year exonerated new DNA evidence His case represents longest duration incarceration case overturned DNA evidence longest-serving inmate exonerated North Carolina.On September 6 1976 two woman found dead Elizabethtown North Carolina Both multiple stab wound injury indicating violent struggle.Joseph Sledge Jr. 34 year old recently escaped minimum-security White Lake Prison Camp September 5 suspected police issued warrant arrest Sledge spotted September 7 driving stolen '69 Chevrolet Fayetteville eventually escaped foot extended car chase The next day arrested Dillion brought questioning Sledge serving 4-year sentence misdemeanour larceny claimed jumped fence escape prison camp due beating threat life He led police escaped showed escape route stolen car Sledge sent back prison The police interviewed prisoner Sledge subsequently spent time prison following murder February 1978 formally charged two inmate Herman Baker Donnie Sutton claimed confessed crime prison.During trial May year Sledge denied committed crime two day deliberation trial resulted hung jury Sledge set trial August 1978 however time jury convicted second-degree murder received two back-to-back life sentences.He appealed North Carolina Supreme Court next year effort failed acquit crime.Sledge continued file post-conviction motion prison declining help lawyer He eventually filed 25 prison length incarceration one sworn statement former inmate Herman Baker claimed Baker admitted lied oath result police coercion promised favor However none motion succeeded bringing investigation exoneration In 2003 Sledge requested DNA testing conducted hair evidence found case however evidence gone missing 2012 evidence surfaced tested Mitochondrial DNA testing pubic hair evidence match Sledge.In 2013 Baker came forward recanted story saying testimony false Sutton lied receiving special treatment share $ 5000 reward Governor 's Office offered return information leading arrest conviction He admitted promised early parole $ 3000 received Additionally Baker claimed police described scene testimony would believable Sutton deceased time record show also received early parole reward $ 2,000 The North Carolina Center Actual Innocence helped investigate case also learned prosecution shown jury key evidence put Sledge 's guilt doubt For instance initial interview Sutton denied Sledge admitted crime later changed story They also discovered case prosecution also failed tell jury second suspect lived 500 yard away shoe print found resembled bloody print found Davis house two woman killed.On January 25 2015 Sledge declared 'factually innocent panel three North Carolina Superior Court Judges released He prison crime 36 year making Sledge longest serving inmate exonerated DNA evidence longest serving inmate exonerated North Carolina The decision made Sledge would receive $ 750,000 recompense wrongful incarceration The current District Attorney Bladen County although prosecutor time original trial apologised Sledge saying “ There 's nothing worse prosecutor convicting innocent person. ” He also stated case would re-opened find real killer.Christine Mumma director North Carolina Center Actual Innocence accused inappropriate professional conduct case took water bottle home Marie Andrus DNA test performed without permission Mumma received official admonition lowest form warning available disciplinary panel The evidence came back inconclusive used exonerate Sledge Joseph Sledge eighth inmate freed based investigation North Carolina Center Actual Innocence.Days eventual exoneration Caroline Brown granddaughter victim Josephine Davis expressed disgust possibility impending release still believing guilty 10 In interview released Sledge stated My personal opinion made scapegoat one blame And I escapee prison unit two lady killed kind fixed manner make look like perpetrator.He also expressed opinion practice using hair analysis evidence guilt crime abolished 11 Sledge later sued prosecuted case blaming nine people well Columbus County Clerk Court Bladen County Sheriff ’ Office State Bureau Investigation holding failing find DNA evidence would exonerated much earlier 12 13 The Bladen County sheriff ’ office eventually settled suit paying Sledge $ 4 million 14 15 Additional lawsuit continue State North Carolina action SBI Clerk 's Office Sledge alleges ignored plea DNA testing 16 17

contemporary text volume scope It compilation many type text including simple genealogical information psychologically rich biography ancestor member noble family fable schwanks droll story facetiae comic and/or erotic short story .The purpose work probably twofold Firstly Froben Christopher wanted prove nobility family preserve knowledge posterity Secondly chronicle mean educate future family member The author tell story shining example nobility also give proof bad example He clearly condemns spendthrift ancestor selling family good hence giving away economic political power.The Zimmern Chronicle begin history Cimbri ancient Germanic tribe tell story Cimbri 's forced relocation Black Forest reign Charlemagne While link Cimbri Zimmern family fictional induced similar-sounding name Froben recount several episode woven stream historical information prove The work also includes complete fictional genealogy starting 10th century Historical evidence entered first actually known family member Konrad von Zimmern abbot Reichenau Abbey c. 1234 1255 Starting early 14th century genealogical historical part Zimmern Chronicle finally reduced fact Still Froben insert entertaining story enliven characterization prove political points.In 1540 Froben Christopher written genealogical Liber rerum Cimbriacarum whose structure show many resemblance later work.The beginning chronicle know today lie probably year 1559 even finished Froben Christopher 's death 1566.Two manuscript written secretary Johannes Müller Froben Christopher 's chancellery Meßkirch Castle With Zimmern family expiring death Froben Christopher 's male heir Wilhelm von Zimmern early 1594 work never materialized memorial textbook originally intended become The chronicle manuscript eventually wound possession Feenstra 450 U.S. 455 1981 United States Supreme Court case Court held Louisiana Head Master law gave sole control marital property husband indicate husband 's dominance wife marriage unconstitutional.In 1974 Joan Feenstra charged husband Harold molested daughter Harold hired attorney Karl Kirchberg defend charge mortgaged Feenstras home toward paying cost attorney Joan informed mortgage Head Master provision Louisiana law allowed without consent knowledge She dropped charge couple separated Joan learn mortgage 1976 Harold 's attorney returned demand payment threatened foreclosure She filed lawsuit arguing Louisiana 's law giving sole control marital property husband unconstitutional.The district court upheld Louisiana 's law On appeal Fifth Circuit overturned district court finding law unconstitutionally violated Equal Protection Clause limited application ruling future decision Feenstra appealed Supreme Court.Applying intermediate scrutiny Craig v. Title: Río Piedras massacre
Content: The Río Piedras massacre occurred October 24 1935 University Puerto Rico Río Piedras Puerto Rico Police officer confronted opened fire supporter Puerto Rican Nationalist Party Four Nationalist Party member killed one police officer wounded shooting.In 1931 U.S.-appointed Governor Puerto Rico Theodore Roosevelt Jr. named Dr. Carlos E. Chardón Chancellor University Puerto Rico He first Puerto Rican position In 1935 Chardón initiated project based idea Luis Muñoz Marín time Senator Puerto Rican legislature member Liberal Party Puerto Rico It known Reconstruction Puerto Rico Project The plan within New Deal criterion established U.S. President Franklin Delano Roosevelt Great Depression well received became known Plan Chardón.Pedro Albizu Campos president Puerto Rican Nationalist Party knew Roosevelt implicated Assistant Secretary Navy helping Secretary Albert Fall Department Interior arrange private leasing Navy oil field became known Teapot Dome Scandal 1920s Albizu Campos worried Plan Chardón would strip Puerto Rico natural resource He believed Chardón placed charge Puerto Rico Reconstruction Administration PRRA order Americanize university support Liberal Party On October 20 1935 political meeting Nationalist Party held town Maunabo transmitted radio Albizu Campos denounced Chardón university dean Liberal Party traitor saying wanted convert university American propaganda institution.On October 23 1935 group student university supported Chardón began collect signature petition declare Albizu Campos Student Enemy Number One In turn protest group pro-Nationalist faction student denounced Chardón Liberal Party agent United States.On October 24 1935 student assembly held university declared Albizu Campos persona non grata Chardón requested governor provide armed Puerto Rico Police officer university ground case situation turned violent Two police officer spotted suspicious-looking vehicle asked driver Ramón S. Pagán friend Pedro Quiñones identification A struggle ensued police killed Pagán Quiñones The local newspaper El Mundo reported October 25 day observer heard explosion followed gunfire Eduardo Rodríguez Vega José Santiago Barea also killed day.An eyewitness Isolina Rondón testified saw police officer shooting victim heard one police officer screaming let escape alive Her testimony ignored charge filed police officer The Río Piedras massacre left four men dead.The supporter Nationalist Party killed shooting A bystander Nationalist also killed Among wounded At time massacre top-ranking U.S.-appointed police chief island former U.S. Army Colonel named Elisha Francis Riggs Colonel Elisha Francis Riggs born Georgetown northwest Washington D.C. appointed Chief Police Puerto Rico 1933 Blanton Winship U.S. appointed governor Puerto Rico He unpopular police chief stemming decision repress growing organized labor movement among sugar cane worker Nationalist Pro-Independence Movement Since entire Puerto Rico Police took order Colonel Riggs Nationalist Party considered responsible massacre 11 On February 23 1936 Colonel Riggs assassinated Nationalists Hiram Rosado Elías Beauchamp member Cadets Republic paramilitary wing Nationalist Party They attacked fatally shot police chief returning home attending Mass San Juan 's Cathedral Rosado Beauchamp arrested either subjected summary execution shot attempting escape Puerto Rico Police headquarters San Juan Before death Beauchamp posed giving military salute news photographer 12 News assassination spread throughout United States The Puerto Rican Senator Luis Muñoz Marín Washington D.C. time asked Ernest Gruening administrator Puerto Rico Reconstruction Administration 1935–1937 publicly condemn Col. Riggs 's assassination Senator Muñoz Marín declined unless also allowed condemn Puerto Rico Police allegedly executing two assassin without trial.Gruening joined US Senator Millard Tydings Maryland Democrat 1943 legislative proposal grant independence Puerto Rico Although measure welcomed every political party Puerto Rico including Muñoz Liberal Party senator opposed measure Senator Muñoz Marín said independence would hurt Puerto Rico 's economy He contrasted proposed bill provision Tydings–McDuffie Act provided independence Philippines 10-year transition period Due opposition bill progress Congress Puerto Rico receive political independence U.S.In 1950 81st United States Congress passed legislation enable people Puerto Rico organize local government pursuant constitution comparable territory state United States From enactment day act served organic law government Puerto Rico relation United States Muñoz Marín Governor Puerto Rico supported measure Muñoz Marín became first native-born elected governor Puerto Rico 13 After Col. Riggs 's assassination many Nationalist Party leader imprisoned Members Puerto Rican independence movement came greater scrutiny prosecution Among leader arrested Pedro Albizu Campos Juan Antonio Corretjer Luis F. Velazquez Clemente Soto Vélez Erasmo Velazquez Julio H. Velazquez Juan Gallardo Santiago Juan Juarbe Juarbe Pablo Rosado Ortiz They later released $ 10,000 bail The Nationalist Rafael Ortiz Pacheco fled Dominican Republic.These leader charged conspired overthrow U.S. government island They tried U.S. District Court Old San Juan Puerto Rico The first trial jury included minority Puerto Ricans among member ended hung jury A second jury picked consisting solely Anglo-Americans This jury found every Nationalist charged guilty exception Juarbe Juarbe The guilty finding sentence appealed U.S. Court Appeals First Circuit Boston MA affirmed lower court ’ determination 14

Title: Edward Montagu, 1st Earl of Sandwich
Content: Edward Montagu 1st Earl Sandwich KG PC FRS JP 27 July 1625 – 28 May 1672 English military officer politician diplomat fought Parliamentarian army First English Civil War MP various time 1645 died 1676 described religious virtuous woman loving contenting heart desire .On 7 November 1642 Montagu married Jemima Crew daughter John Crew 1st Baron Crew Jemima Waldegrave Pepys Diary refers great Paulina 's death February 1669 aged twenty great source grief father Pepys called peevish lady called pay condolence found shut away sorrow .Although father Royalist First English Civil War began August 1642 Montagu followed Parliamentarian cousin Earl Manchester served Eastern Association He raised regiment infantry 1644 campaign fought Marston Moor Siege York Second Newbury Despite family relationship Montagu supported Parliament expressed dissatisfaction conduct war Manchester Earl Essex.This resulted creation New Model Army February 1645 passing Self-denying Ordinance requiring holding military commission resign Parliament As member House Lords Manchester Essex automatically removed since unlike MPs could resign title Montagu 's regiment incorporated New Model taking part June 1645 Battle Naseby followed capture Bristol In October resigned army required Ordinance appointed MP Huntingdonshire seat formerly held father died September 1644.Montagu played part Second held father died September 1644 He also appointed English Council State office held dissolved 1659 re-elected First Protectorate Parliament 1654 Second Protectorate Parliament 1656.During Anglo-Spanish War 1654–1660 appointed joint General Sea Robert Blake taking part expedition Mediterranean This experience made leading advocate establishing British naval base region ambition realised acquisition English Tangier 1661 In February 1657 one so-called New Cromwellians supported Humble Petition Advice inviting Cromwell declare king advocating re-establishment national church The measure opposed army radical including Charles Fleetwood John Lambert ultimately rejected.In June 1658 commanded naval squadron blockaded Dunkirk Cromwell died September Montagu remained loyal son appointed successor Richard Cromwell During brief disastrous rule Lord Protector Montagu remained sea early 1659 sent mediate Sweden Denmark however suspected secret communication exiled Charles II republican Title: Brian Charrington
Content: Brian Charrington born 1956 English drug trafficker owner car dealership Middlesbrough along Curtis Cocky Warren operated North East England late-1980s eventually built criminal empire link neighboring Colombian drug cartel smuggle large amount cocaine steel box concealed lead ingot Great Britain Although one ingot examined first shipment custom official allowed shipment pas through.However later notified Dutch police custom stopped second shipment contained 907 kg cocaine Charrington Warren twenty-six others placed arrest early 1992 Despite Charrington 's status informant North-East Regional Crime Squad custom official went forward prosecution despite protest handler Harry Knaggs Ian Weedon Eventually Tory MP Tim Devlin meeting arranged Customs ordered drop charge Charrington 28 January 1993 several month later Knaggs allegedly noticed custom official driving £70,000 BMW registered Charrington .Although British authority unable bring trial Manchester involvement smuggling cocaine worth estimated £150 million Britain 's security force admitted supergrass Colombian cartel re-homed Australia visa revoked shortly arrival Traveling Spain resided Costa Blanca resort Calpe later fortified villa laundered million pound used bring hashish Morocco across border continued sell.During late-1990s Charrington would continue court Bristol Crown Court acquitted charge found custom officer illegally boarded boat carrying 4 ton hashish worth £80 million 1999 Illegally re-entering country see family 2002 arrested police near Exeter placed trial Leeds Crown Court involving two suspended detective former detective would dismissed judge refused admit phone tap recording evidence.Soon court appearance warrant issued Bow Street Magistrates Court extradition Germany July 2003 Charrington sentenced seven year Frankfurt Germany conspiracy smuggle cocaine Germany phone recording linking Charrington smuggling operation run son Brian Charrington Jr. served four year three month used conviction In January 2009 Brian Charrington attacked Brian Charrington Jr. hospitalised This created bitter rivalry two issued death threats.Following release 2006 extradited France serve two-year prison term 650 kilo hashish found possession yacht English Channel 1995.In civil suit filed Assets Recovery Agency ARA 2004 government agency ruled asset seized Charrington Warren following trial 1992 acquired result criminal activity specifically money laundering people trafficking Although men claimed ownership estimated £3.6 million earlier denied ownership following seizure original £2.2 million Charrington 's residence Middlesbrough HM Customs & Excise 1992.After Charrington 's claim money earned legitimate diamond dealing rejected three month earlier High Court believed laundering money Mario Halley Warren allowed additional time provide evidence back claim however appeal also rejected 6 October Subsequently ARA granted largest Civil Recovery Order proceeds going towards funding government crime reduction programs.In 2018 Charrington detained Spanish police Spanish national police recovered 220 kilo cocaine allegedly hidden luxury villa Spain In November 2018 Charrington ordered serve 15-year prison sentence court Alicante Spain.The Spanish press referred Charrington el narco que escribía en Wikipedia English translation narco Title: Red Sea Insurance Co Ltd v Bouygues SA
Content: Red Sea Insurance Co Ltd v Bouygues SA 1995 1 AC 190 judicial decision Privy Council relating choice law tort The case appeal decision Court Appeal Hong Kong case decided Hong Kong pursuant English Law Ordinance section 3 1 also taken authoritative statement English law.Bouygues SA together nine co-plaintiffs made claim policy insurance Red Sea Insurance Co Ltd. Red Sea Insurance insurance company incorporated Hong Kong head office located Saudi Arabia In counterclaim Red Sea Insurance alleged one co-plaintiffs PCG negligently supplied faulty pre-cast concrete building unit liable Red Sea Insurance would subrogated claim co-plaintiffs PCG PCG applied strike counterclaim.Red Sea amended pleading claimed proper law governing relation Red Sea PCG law Saudi Arabia Saudi Arabian law Red Sea direct right action PCG.Those claim failed first instance Court Appeal Red Sea appealed Privy Council.Lord Slynn Hadley gave decision board.After reviewing relevant authority Lord Slynn held flexible exception double actionability requirement created House Lords Boys v Chaplin 1971 AC 356 could apply favour forum lex fori also favour law place tort occurred lex locus delicti commissi In case fact overwhelmingly connected Saudi Arabia Saudi Arabian law applied relevant issue.Lord Slynn held although Boys v Chaplin predicated single issue head loss subject flexible exception possible entire claim could subject exception He stated The present appeal based isolated issue case Boys v Chaplin The contention put forward whole case decided according lex locus delictii Although case may rare exception applied whole case Lordships consider apply exception whole case principle necessarily excluded In Lordship 's view exception limited specific isolated issue may apply whole claim .In England decision followed Court Appeal Pearce v Ove Arup Partnership Ltd 2000 Ch 403 largely superseded Private International Law Miscellaneous Provisions Act 1995 However remains good law common law jurisdiction England claim relating defamation.In Canada double actionability rule reversed Supreme Court Canada Tolofson v Jensen 1994 3 SCR 1022 although Supreme Court retained concept flexible exception.Similarly Australia double actionability rule abrogated High Court Australia John Pfieffer Pty Ltd v Rogerson 2000 203 CLR 503 But similarly broad public policy style flexible exception similar Red Sea Insurance v Bouygues SA retained

Title: USS Aniwa
Content: USS Aniwa ID-3146 steel-hulled single-screw freighter served United States Navy 1918 1919.Aniwa Design 1015 ship built United States Shipping Board contract completed SS Aniwa 1918 Oakland California Moore Shipbuilding Company She earmarked U.S. Navy World War I service naval registry Identification Number Id No 3146 She departed builder 's yard final sea trial morning 25 July 1918 arrived San Francisco California afternoon On morning 26 July 1918 Aniwa commissioned USS Aniwa'.Aniwa moved Mare Island Navy Yard Vallejo California 27 July 1918 take store embark balance crew She moved Port Costa California 31 July 1918 loaded cargo flour Underway United States East Coast 7 August 1918 Aniwa transited Panama Canal 23 August 1918 clearing Cristóbal Panama Canal Zone early 24 August 1918 shaped course New York City She reached Brooklyn New York afternoon 4 September 1918.Earlier 1918 United States Ambassador Russia David R. Francis urged sending shipload foodstuff Archangel North Russia three-fold purpose 1 feed local Russian population whose flow provision interrupted Czech Legion 's occupation Trans-Siberian Railway 2 provide Allied representative city Vologda Russia retire northward 3 create favorable image United States Russia Accordingly shortly midday 15 September 1918 Aniwa headed sea cargo flour convoy bound ultimately Archangel.Aniwa arrived mouth Dvina River 11 October 1918 ascended river 12 October 1918 At 17:45 hour day made fast alongside British merchant ship SS Grofe Castle turn moored wharf Archangel Aniwa immediately posted watch bow stern protect Aniwa cargo On 14 October 1918 four soldiers—a corporal three privates—reported Aniwa serve armed guard.An outbreak influenza Archangel curtailed shore leave Aniwa 's crew certain period ship 's stay It even struck Aniwa 's hospital corpsman sent ashore treatment American Red Cross hospital To fill gap created illness ship doctor U.S. Navy cargo ship USS West Gambo ID-3220 U.S. Navy cruiser USS Olympia Cruiser No 6 visited Aniwa ministered sick.Unloading operation proceeded nearly without incident However afternoon 23 October 1918 two Russian stevedore obviously feeling shortage foodstuff ashore caught trying leave ship small quantity Aniwa 's cargo flour Then 5 November 1918 sling broke dropping bale hemp Russian stevedore Fortunately badly hurt soon way Russian hospital treatment.Aniwa got underway United States ballast morning 10 November 1918 small number passenger embarked World War I ended following day.Aniwa reached Brooklyn 8 December 1918 Shifting Bush Terminal Brooklyn soon thereafter loaded 6,905 ton general cargo underwent minor repairs.Assigned Naval Overseas Transportation Service Aniwa cleared port New York shortly midday 29 December 1918 bound Gibraltar As day wore weather remained fairly rough ship rolling easily long swell took water forward aft leak storeroom occupied attention least one man nearly entire day 7 January 1919 Soon thereafter problem condenser boiler forced put Azores 10 January 1919 voyage repairs.Underway 28 January 1919 Aniwa reached Gibraltar 4 February 1919 remained short resuming voyage Genoa Italy arrived morning 11 February 1919.Inept cargo handling unloading operation Genoa caused much damage shipment foodstuff Aniwa carried New York Finally early March discharged brought took ammunition U.S. Navy tug USS Nahant SP-1250 USS Penobscot SP-982 transportation back United States loaded ballast return trip She departed Genoa morning 17 March 1919.After touching briefly Gibraltar 23 March 1919 24 March 1919 pick passenger Aniwa arrived Tompkinsville Staten Island New York 15 April 1919 There unloaded ammunition She soon moved pier East 19th Street New York City She decommissioned 21 April 1919 name struck Navy List day.Turned United States Shipping Board operation ship SS Aniwa continued carrying cargo civilian auspex During remainder 1919 called Mobile Alabama Liverpool England Newport News Virginia.Aniwa laid 1923 remained inactive discarded due age deterioration fiscal year 1930
